    {
      "id": "d90407a4_49d65dd2",
      "file_path": "cps-ncmp-service/src/test/groovy/org/onap/cps/ncmp/impl/datajobs/subscription/cmavc/CmAvcEventExactlyOnceIntegrationSpec.groovy",
      "patchset_number": 3,
      "line": 193,
      "message": "can we simulate that not the first send throws the exception, but let's say the 250th event send throws the exception?\n\nSo not the whole sendCloudEventBatch is overriden, but with a mockitospybean you can listen to the invocation of cloudEventKafkaTemplateForExactlyOnceSemantics.send() calls in EventProducer class, and return with a failed CompletableFuture that contains a KafkaException.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 8559,
        "name": "Daniel Molnar",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "dani.molnar2001@gmail.com",
        "username": "molnardani"
      },
      "updated": "2026-04-30 07:35:18.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "8d223008_b2243b3b",
      "file_path": "cps-ncmp-service/src/test/groovy/org/onap/cps/ncmp/impl/datajobs/subscription/cmavc/CmAvcEventExactlyOnceIntegrationSpec.groovy",
      "patchset_number": 3,
      "line": 193,
      "message": "Hi Daniel, it might be possible, but does it really add value?! \nIt might be a lot of effort but whether the first batch fails or a later batch it should not matter for the recovery algorithm....\nThe integration test is to prove that we have configured the Kaka correctly, not the detail behavior of Kafka itself,  It would be like testing a java Array Sort algorithm or something like that with many variations, we should be able to trust our 3PPs, they have their own tests... If we don't, our testware would explode to an unmaintainable level...",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 6639,
        "name": "Toine Siebelink",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "toine.siebelink@est.tech",
        "username": "ToineSiebelink"
      },
      "updated": "2026-04-30 08:05:55.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "d90407a4_49d65dd2",
      "unresolved": true
    },
